## 14. WHAT THE OLD LIFeOS SPEC HAD THAT YVON OS IS MISSING

### Core UX patterns
Live count badges on every sidebar nav item — the most important missing pattern. The entire system is built around "surfacing what needs you."
Global command/search box — fastest navigation across 33 pages
Machine/fleet infrastructure view — currently on wrong page (Agents page)
Per-workspace visual theming — currently only accent colors; spec calls for distinct design per workspace

### Agent system depth
13 agent personality baselines — documented but not injected into agent system
Agent workflows — Henry filtering, Nexus PRs-only, Steve QA gate, Knox security — all design intent, none implemented
Learning behavior — agents auto-handle more over time as they learn owner decisions

### Screen-level features
9 stub pages that need full implementations (see Priority Matrix)
Force-directed 3D graph in Brain & Wiki
Per-workspace rooms in Office
Contact intelligence in Inbox
Lead/deal pipeline in Consulting CRM
Client project tracker in Cinematic Sites